{"TopicId":138435,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Heat ripple effect.","CreatedByName":"Tricky14","CreatedById":145768,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T07:45:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Tricky14","CreatedById":145768,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T07:45:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould it be possible to add some kind of heat ripple effect from exhaust jets under Unity 5? Under atmosphere only, of course. A slight ripple effect might work for overheated parts too. Or a bit randomly here and there in hot atmospheric biomes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really a request, but anyone can claim it and build it up if they feel like it. I\u0027m mostly curious about Unity 5.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/JpR4kbz.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022JpR4kbz.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MrHappyFace","CreatedById":76365,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T17:11:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s always been possible, Unity 5 or not. There\u0027s an atmospheric heat ripple effect in my mod Kopernicus Expansion, but\u00A0I don\u0027t think there\u0027s an engine heat refraction mod yet, though it\u0027d be pretty trivial to make one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-29T17:12:12Z\u0022 title=\u002204/29/2016 05:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by MrHappyFace\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T17:16:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngood way to make KSP use some of that untapped GPU power. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cxg2827","CreatedById":57380,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T17:47:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw this a while ago.\u00A0Not sure if \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/72433-bahamutod/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002272433\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/72433-bahamutod/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@BahamutoD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is still working on it\u003C/span\u003E:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://gfycat.com/PleasingGratefulBluetickcoonhound\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://gfycat.com/PleasingGratefulBluetickcoonhound\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-29T22:54:13Z\u0022 title=\u002204/29/2016 10:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by cxg2827\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rbray89","CreatedById":48847,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T00:16:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow that we have command buffers, it should actually be surprisingly easy to do. I have a few things I\u0027d like to add before I get there though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tricky14","CreatedById":145768,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T07:40:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeat. I hope this will happen some day.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022^_^\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022^_^\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}